rComments: For first year, you won't have much of a choice. That said, Dube's not a bad prof. Lectures are kinda dry, mandatory graded problems in the tutorials. Study the slides, go over old problems, and a bit of practice is all you need. The final 2 sections isn't easy, so pay attention. Overall very reasonable.

The Prof is an incredibly nice guy and actually makes an effort to get to know his students. He knew most of our names and was always willing to answer questions. However, his lectures were very boring, and the examples in class are hard to follow. I thought I had done well in the exam when in fact, I almost failed it. Lectures don't really help.

The professor was quite useless as a teacher. Didn't captivate my interest. Went to see him once for help and it took him 55 mins and 4 tries to solve a question he had given us in the assignment. The class itself is quite nice but he is not a very good professor
A very helpful and nice professor outside of the classroom. He's intelligent and knows his stuff. Lectures however are slightly boring and a bit hard to learn from.

Well, to be honest you don't really need to attend his class at all, because his voice is so monotone that you will probably fall asleep anyways, and the textbook is pretty easy to follow. Overall, he does a fine job in teaching I guess, his midterms are pretty fair, finals can be tough but doable if you read the textbook and do a lot of problems.

A very helpful professor, he does the best he can with this course he teaches (which admittedly has a fair amount of dry content - no pun intended for those who have taken this course). Exams are very fair, the only thing wrong with the course is that the TA's are not very helpful in the tutorial session.
One of the best professors in the department, could put more effort though.
Very good professor in general and very helpful. The only thing you have to watch out for is the difficulty of his final exam. Class average was ~57% in Winter 2011 semester.
Great Professor

This is second class I've had with him, so I'm used to his teaching style. May be boring at times, but teaches well with relevant examples. Exams are really hard though so make sure you understand everything really well.

He has this little alarm that rings every 20 minutes so that everyone can have a brake, (optimises concentration he says). Very clear, helpful and cool prof.Very easy midterm and assignments. Final exam is not that easy but is still fair.
The assignments really helped for the exam.  I like his fun, & young spirit!

I find lectures boring because everything is in the lecture notes. I'm just reading off the notes in class... I could read them at home! Very nice prof, but could try to make class more interesting. :)
Really nice and helpful prof; tries to connect with his students. His examples are solved in the lecture notes, which can make going through them more boring; however, overall he is a great lecturer.
He is OK,
Best prof you could ever come accross!!! TAKE ALL HIS CLASSES he makes the most boring of subjects interesting.  He is very easy to pay attention to.

This guy is awesome. His lectures are actually interesting and the in-class examples keep you paying attention. the course is only as tough as you make it. I suck at physics but this prof somehow managed to get the material through to me. VERY hard final, probably my worst of the 6 i wrote, but the class was still fun nonetheless :)
good with in-class examples.  his comfort level with the material and with teaching a class helps the class run smoothly, very approachable, funny guy
Excellent Prof. This is my third class with him and he's great. He's ver friendly and is always willing to help you or give advice. Excellent course organization, and great in class examples.
Good examples to help understand.A bit boring.
No Comments
Very nice prof.  Clear, reasonable marker, available for questions and concerns.  Do-able assignments.  Can be a kind of high on himself.
Good prof. He can teach! Does a lot of example to help us learn better.  Too monotone.
Nice, friendly, but a bit too monotone
